msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Niẓām al-Dīn al-Nīsābūrī's commentary on Naṣīr al-Dīn al-Ṭūsī's recension of Ptolemy's Almagest. A leaf is likely missing after the first leaf.

author.persName: Nīsābūrī, Niẓām al-Dīn al-Ḥasan ibn Muḥammad, -1328 or 1329
نيسابوري، نظام الدين الحسن بن محمد،
Ṭūsī, Naṣīr al-Dīn Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad, 1201-1274
طوسي، نصير الدين محمد بن محمد،

supportDesc.extent: 213 leaves : 264 x 166 (166 x 95) mm bound to 264 x 180 mm

collation.p: Paper, 213 + i. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a naskh script by Muḥammad ibn al-Ḥusayn al-Ḥasan (colophon, f. 213r).

decoDesc.decoNote: Large astronomical diagram in black ink on iridescent ground (f. 156r); numerous small astronomical diagrams and a few tables (f. 18v-19v) in red ink, some diagrams with additions in gold; a few rubrications in gold, though they end close to the beginning of the text, and blank spaces have been left; overlining in red.

binding.p: Dark brown leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); blind-stamped mandorla on covers and flap; plain paper doublure.

origin.p: Possibly written in Persia, now Iran, dated 13 Dhū al-Qaʻdah, A.H. 813 (18 March 1411, colophon, f. 213r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Yāsīn ibn ʻAbd al-Wahhāb al-Siṭrābī (?) (f. 1r).
Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Nov. 2000.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
